    "The next section assessed the socio-demographic features of the participants.",
    "The following variables were assessed: (1) age as a scale variable; (2) sex (male vs. female); (3) current country of residence (Algeria, Bahrain, Djibouti, Egypt, Iraq, Jordan, Kuwait, Lebanon, Libya, Mauritania, Morocco, Oman, Palestine, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Somalia, Sudan, Syria, Tunisia, the United Arab Emirates (UAE), and Yemen); (4) ethnicity (Arab vs. non-Arab); (5) School/College/Faculty (health vs. scientific vs. humanities); (6) University (public vs. private); (7) current educational level (bachelor (BSc) vs. masters (MSc) vs. doctorate (PhD)); (8) The latest grade point average (GPA) (excellent, very good, good, satisfactory, and unsatisfactory).",
